{"title_page": "Russian Futsal Super League", "text_new": "{{Infobox football league\n| logo       =\u0421\u0443\u043f\u0435\u0440\u043b\u0438\u0433\u0430\u0410\u041c\u0424\u0420.png\n| pixels     = 140\n| country    = Russia\n| confed     = UEFA\n| rank       =\n| founded    = 1991\n| teams      = 10\n| relegation =\n| levels     = 1\n| domest_cup = [[Russian Futsal Cup]]\n| confed_cup = [[UEFA Futsal Cup]]\n| champions  = [[MFK Tyumen]]\n| season     = 1\n| most successful club = [[MFK Dinamo Moskva|Dinamo Moscow]] (11)\n| website    = {{URL|http://www.amfr.ru|AMFR.ru}}\n| current    = [[Russian futsal championship 2018/2019|2018/2019]]\n}}\n\nThe '''Russian Futsal Super League''' (Russian: ''\u0427\u0435\u043c\u043f\u0438\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0442 \u0420\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0438 \u043f\u043e \u043c\u0438\u043d\u0438-\u0444\u0443\u0442\u0431\u043e\u043b\u0443 (\u0421\u0443\u043f\u0435\u0440\u043b\u0438\u0433\u0430)'') is the premier professional [[futsal]] league in [[Russia]]. It was founded in 1991. The '''Super League''', which is played under [[UEFA]] rules, currently consists of 14 teams, including teams like [[MFK Dina Moskva|Dina Moscow]] - 3-times European club championship and 1997 Intercontinental Cup winner, [[MFK Dinamo Moskva|Dinamo Moscow oblast]] - [[UEFA Futsal Cup 2006\u201307]] winner and 2013 Intercontinental Cup winner, [[Viz-Sinara Ekaterinburg|Sinara Ekaterinburg]] - [[UEFA Futsal Cup 2007\u201308]] winner, [[Gazprom-Ugra Yugorsk|Gazprom-Ugra]] [[2015\u201316 UEFA Futsal Cup]] winner. <ref>http://www.sportstats.com/futsal/russia/superliga-2012-2013/standings/</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Season\n!Champions\n!2nd place\n!3rd place\n|-\n|[[1991 Soviet Futsal Super League|1991]]\n|'''[[MFK GKI-Gazprom Moskva|KSM-24]]''' (Moscow) ('''1''')\n|[[MFK Metallurg Aldan|Metallurg]] ([[Aldan, Russia|Aldan]])\n|[[MFK Agros-Intex|Agros-Intex]] ([[Chi\u015fin\u0103u]])\n|-\n|[[1992 CIS Futsal Super League|1992]]\n|'''[[MFK Dina Moskva|Dina]] '''(Moscow)\n|[[MFK Spartak Moskva|Spartak]] (Moscow)\n|[[MFK Stroitel|Stroitel]] ([[Verh-Neyvinsk]])\n|-\n|[[1992\u201393 Russian Futsal Super League|1992-93]]\n|'''[[MFK Dina Moskva|Dina]] '''(Moscow)\n|[[MFK Dina-MAB Moskva|Dina-MAB]] (Moscow)\n|[[MFK Fenix Chelyabinsk|Fenix]] ([[Chelyabinsk]])\n|-\n|[[1993\u201394 Russian Futsal Super League|1993-94]]\n|'''[[MFK Dina Moskva|Dina]] '''(Moscow)\n|[[MFK Fenix Chelyabinsk|Fenix]] (Chelyabinsk)\n|[[MFK GKI-Gazprom Moskva|KSM-24]] (Moscow)\n|-\n|[[1994\u201395 Russian Futsal Super League|1994-95]]\n|'''[[MFK Dina Moskva|Dina]] '''(Moscow)\n|[[MFK Minkas Moskva|Minkas]] (Moscow)\n|[[MFK VIZ-Sinara Yekaterinburg|VIZ]] ([[Yekaterinburg]])\n|-\n|[[1995\u201396 Russian Futsal Super League|1995-96]]\n|'''[[MFK Dina Moskva|Dina]] '''(Moscow)\n|[[MFK GKI-Gazprom Moskva|KSM-24]] (Moscow)\n|[[MFK TTG-Java Yugorsk|TTG]] ([[Yugorsk]])\n|-\n|[[1996\u201397 Russian Futsal Super League|1996-97]]\n|'''[[MFK Dina Moskva|Dina]] '''(Moscow)\n|[[MFK GKI-Gazprom Moskva|GKI-Gazprom]] (Moscow)\n|[[MFK TTG-Java Yugorsk|TTG-Java]] (Yugorsk)\n|-\n|[[1997\u201398 Russian Futsal Super League|1997-98]]\n|'''[[MFK Dina Moskva|Dina]] '''(Moscow)\n|[[MFK VIZ-Sinara Yekaterinburg|VIZ-Sinara]] (Yekaterinburg)\n|[[MFK GKI-Gazprom Moskva|GKI-Gazprom]] (Moscow)\n|-\n|[[1998\u201399 Russian Futsal Super League|1998-99]]\n|'''[[MFK Dina Moskva|Dina]] '''(Moscow)\n|[[MFK VIZ-Sinara Yekaterinburg|VIZ-Sinara]] (Yekaterinburg)\n|[[MFK Minkas Moskva|Minkas]] (Moscow)\n|-\n|[[1999\u20132000 Russian Futsal Super League|1999-00]]\n|'''[[MFK Dina Moskva|Dina]] '''(Moscow)\n|[[MFK Spartak Moskva|Spartak]] (Moscow)\n|[[MFK GKI-Gazprom Moskva|GKI-Gazprom]] (Moscow)\n|-\n|[[2000\u201301 Russian Futsal Super League|2000-01]]\n|'''[[MFK Spartak Moskva|Spartak]] '''(Moscow) ('''1''')\n|[[MFK Norilsk Nickel|Norilsky Nikel]] ([[Norilsk]])\n|[[MFK TTG-Java Yugorsk|TTG-Java-Java]] (Yugorsk)\n|-\n|[[2001\u201302 Russian Futsal Super League|2001-02]]\n|'''[[MFK Norilsk Nickel|Norilsky