ues established in 1991]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football league\n| logo       =\u0421\u0443\u043f\u0435\u0440\u043b\u0438\u0433\u0430\u0410\u041c\u0424\u0420.png\n| pixels     = 140\n| country    = Russia\n| confed     = UEFA\n| rank       =\n| founded    = 1991\n| teams      = 10\n| relegation =\n| levels     = 1\n| domest_cup = [[Russian Futsal Cup]]\n| confed_cup = [[UEFA Futsal Cup]]\n| champions  = [[MFK Tyumen]]\n| season     = 1\n| most successful club = [[MFK Dinamo Moskva|Dinamo Moscow]] (11)\n| website    = {{URL|http://www.amfr.ru|AMFR.ru}}\n| current    = [[Russian futsal championship 2018/2019|2018/2019]]\n}}\n\nThe '''Russian Futsal Super League''' (Russian ''\u0427\u0435\u043c\u043f\u0438\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0442 \u0420\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0438 \u043f\u043e \u043c\u0438\u043d\u0438-\u0444\u0443\u0442\u0431\u043e\u043b\u0443 (\u0421\u0443\u043f\u0435\u0440\u043b\u0438\u0433\u0430)'') is the premier professional [[futsal]] league in [[Russia]]. It was founded in 1991. The '''Super League''', which is played under [[UEFA]] rules, currently consists of 14 teams, including teams like [[MFK Dina Moskva|Dina Moscow]] - 3-times European club championship and 1997 Intercontinental Cup winner, [[MFK Dinamo Moskva|Dinamo Moscow oblast]] - [[UEFA Futsal Cup 2006\u201307]] winner and 2013 Intercontinental Cup winner, [[Viz-Sinara Ekaterinburg|Sinara Ekaterinburg]] - [[UEFA Futsal Cup 2007\u201308]] winner, [[Gazprom-Ugra Yugorsk|Gazprom-Ugra]] [[2015\u201316 UEFA Futsal Cup]] winner. <ref>http://www.sportstats.com/futsal/russia/superliga-2012-2013/standings/</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Season\n!Champions\n!2nd place\n!3rd place\n|-\n|[[1991 Soviet Futsal Super League|1991]]\n|'''[[MFK GKI-Gazprom Moskva|KSM-24]]''' (Moscow) ('''1''')\n|[[MFK Metallurg Aldan|Metallurg]] ([[Aldan, Russia|Aldan]])\n|[[MFK Agros-Intex|Agros-Intex]] ([[Chi\u015fin\u0103u]])\n|-\n|[[1992 CIS Futsal Super League|1992]]\n|'''[[MFK Dina Moskva|Dina]] '''(Moscow)\n|[[MFK Spar